<!doctype html>
<html class="dark" lang="sk">
<head>
  <%- include('../components/head', { title: 'Velocity | About' }) %>
</head>
<body class="bg-surface text-on-surface" data-page="about" id="top">
<%- include('../components/header') %>

<main class="kz-subpage kz-subpage--about">
  <section class="kz-page-hero kz-page-hero--about">
    <div class="kz-page-hero__media">
      <img src="/assets/img/rana-singh.webp" alt="Velocity collection" data-parallax="0.015" />
      <div class="kz-page-hero__overlay"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="kz-shell kz-page-hero__content">
      <span class="kz-page-hero__eyebrow">About us</span>
      <h1>The same cinematic language,<br>translated into every drive.</h1>
      <p>Velocity is not built like a marketplace. It behaves like a private collection—with fewer distractions, cleaner curation, and a stronger point of view.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="kz-editorial kz-shell">
    <div class="kz-section-label js-reveal" data-reveal>
      <span></span>
      <p>Our ethos</p>
    </div>
    <div class="kz-editorial__grid">
      <div class="kz-editorial__headline js-reveal" data-reveal>
        <h2 data-word-reveal>We curate movement, not inventory. Every car, every arrival, and every line of the experience is designed to feel intentional.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="kz-editorial__copy js-reveal" data-reveal>
        <p>Velocity was built as an antidote to generic automotive catalogs. We treat every vehicle as an editorial object—where provenance, texture, engineering, and restraint matter as much as outright speed.</p>
        <p>Our studio is guided by atmosphere, not urgency. We favor fewer stories, stronger curation, and the kind of quiet confidence that only craftsmanship can command.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="kz-about-panels kz-shell">
    <article class="kz-about-panel js-reveal" data-reveal>
      <img src="/assets/img/ritual.webp" alt="The ritual" />
      <div>
        <span>The ritual</span>
        <h3>A slower gaze. A sharper standard.</h3>
        <p>We study every panel gap, every tonal reflection, every mechanical note. The goal is not volume—it is resonance. A car should feel inevitable in its presence.</p>
      </div>
    </article>
    <article class="kz-about-panel kz-about-panel--reverse js-reveal" data-reveal>
      <img src="/assets/img/coastal.webp" alt="The route" />
      <div>
        <span>The route</span>
        <h3>The journal now evolves live.</h3>
        <p>The journal area is no longer a placeholder. Admin-written posts now publish directly into the site and flow through the same visual language as the homepage.</p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="kz-quote-band">
    <div class="kz-shell">
      <p>“Speed is merely a metric. Style is identity. The motion between them is where Velocity lives.”</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="kz-journal kz-shell" id="journal-preview">
    <div class="kz-section-head js-reveal" data-reveal>
      <div>
        <div class="kz-section-label kz-section-label--inline">
          <span></span>
          <p>Journal</p>
        </div>
        <p class="kz-section-copy">Published from the admin desk and rendered here automatically.</p>
      </div>
      <a href="/journal" class="kz-pill kz-pill--ghost">View all</a>
    </div>
      <div class="kz-journal__grid">
        <% if (!latestBlogs || !latestBlogs.length) { %>
          <article class="kz-story-card js-reveal" data-reveal>
            <img src="/assets/img/ritual.webp" alt="Story preview one">
            <div>
              <span>Editorial ready</span>
              <h3>The journal is waiting for its first published story.</h3>
              <p>Use the admin journal desk to write, edit, and publish live entries.</p>
            </div>
          </article>
        <% } %>
        <% (latestBlogs || []).forEach((post) => { %>
          <article class="kz-story-card js-reveal" data-reveal>
            <a href="/journal/<%= post.slug %>"><img src="<%= post.image %>" alt="<%= post.title %>"></a>
            <div>
              <span><%= new Date(post.created_at || Date.now()).toLocaleDateString('en-GB') %></span>
              <h3><a href="/journal/<%= post.slug %>"><%= post.title %></a></h3>
              <p><%= post.excerpt %></p>
            </div>
          </article>
        <% }) %>
      </div>
  </section>
</main>

<%- include('../components/footer') %>
<button id="backToTop" type="button" aria-label="Back to top">↑</button>
<script src="/assets/js/app.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
